commText: Rahul and de Kock are at the crease. Rahul is on strike. Bhuvneshwar will open the attack
Bhuvneshwar to Rahul, 1 run, short of a good length and just outside off, Rahul drops it behind square on the off-side for a single
Bhuvneshwar to de Kock, no run, fuller length delivery and well wide of off, de Kock drives it straight to the fielder at mid-off
Bhuvneshwar to de Kock, 1 run, back of a length and angling across the left-hander, chopped away backward of square on the off-side for a single
Bhuvneshwar to Rahul, no run, on a good length and just outside off - Rahul gets a good stride forward and defends it to mid-off
Bhuvneshwar to Rahul, 1 run, fuller length delivery on the pads, nudged to the right of mid-on for a single

Bhuvneshwar to de Kock, no run, shout for a caught behind / LBW, but they don't review, lovely delivery from Bhuvneshwar, nipped back in sharply and caught de Kock in the crease, past the inside edge, flicked the pad and went through to Klaasen. No bat and looked a tad too high for LBW. It pitched outside leg as well
Pat Cummins, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Cummins to Rahul, no run, fuller length delivery outside off, driven crisply and straight to the fielder at cover
Cummins to Rahul, no run, short of a length and angling into the right-hander, turned to the on-side

Cummins to Rahul, SIX, lovely, touch of class from Rahul - pitched up by Cummins, Rahul leans forward, held his shape and then played an exquisite lofted drive over cover, went sailing over the ropes for a maximum
Cummins to Rahul, 1 run, Cummins drags the length back on off, nudged in front of square on the off-side for a single
Cummins to de Kock, 1 run, on a length and at the stumps, de Kock brings the angle into play on the whip behind square on the on-side, but he's picked out deep backward square leg
Cummins to Rahul, 2 runs, back of a length and well wide of off, Rahul stands tall and then punches it behind square on the off-side, comes back for the second run
Bhuvneshwar to de Kock, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Bhuvneshwar to de Kock, out Caught by Nitish Reddy!! That's a splendid catch at deep backward square leg, but the 3rd umpire will have a look. Looks like a clean catch and de Kock is already walking off. He knows it's a clean catch. Just one replay and the 3rd umpire confirms the same - length ball on the pads, de Kock got inside the line and then whipped it over backward square leg, the ball seemed to be soaring over his head, but Nitish stayed calm, timed his jump to perfection and then held on - he then realized that he was stepping onto the ropes, lobs the ball in the air, goes over and then comes back to take the rebound. Another failure for de Kock and LSG have lost an early wicket. de Kock c Nitish Reddy b Bhuvneshwar 2(5)
Marcus Stoinis, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Bhuvneshwar to Stoinis, no run, short of a good length and angling back into the right-hander, Stoinis has his off-stump covered, lifts his bat and lets it go
Bhuvneshwar to Stoinis, 1 run, back of a length and well wide of off, hits Stoinis high on the bat as he looked to crash it past cover, rolls to the left of mid-off for a single
Bhuvneshwar to Rahul, no run, on a good length and just outside off, Rahul gets a good stride forward and finds cover with the drive
Bhuvneshwar to Rahul, no run, tad fuller and just outside off - Rahul prods forward and pushes it to the off-side
Bhuvneshwar to Rahul, 1 run, on a good length and just outside off, Rahul drops it in front of backward point for a single
Spin and it's Shahbaz Ahmed
Shahbaz Ahmed, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Shahbaz Ahmed to Rahul, 1 run, flighted delivery on off, driven down to long-off for a single
Shahbaz Ahmed to Stoinis, 1 run, Shahbaz tosses one on off, punched down to long-off for a single
Shahbaz Ahmed to Rahul, 1 run, Rahul shimmies down the pitch to a well flighted delivery and pushes it to long-off for a single
Shahbaz Ahmed to Stoinis, 1 run, slower and on off, eased down to long-off for a single

Rahul has been given OUT LBW, but he's reviewed it straightaway. The line looked good, did he get a bit of glove on the sweep? Yes, the ball has clearly hit the glove and has then ricocheted onto the pad - the 3rd umpire doesn't need UltraEdge and the original call has been reversed

Shahbaz Ahmed to Rahul, no run, Rahul has been given OUT LBW, but he's reviewed it straightaway. The line looked good, did he get a bit of glove on the sweep? Yes, the ball has clearly hit the glove and has then ricocheted onto the pad - the 3rd umpire doesn't need UltraEdge and the original call has been reversed. Rahul shuffled across and then tried to sweep a pretty straight ball
Shahbaz Ahmed to Rahul, 1 run, pushed through by Shahbaz, Rahul looks to drive and skews a thick inside edge to long-on
Bhuvneshwar to Rahul, leg byes, 1 run, fuller length delivery on the pads, Rahul was looking to flick and fell over on the shot, off the pad and rolled towards square leg
Bhuvneshwar to Stoinis, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Bhuvneshwar to Stoinis, out Caught by Sanvir Singh!! Another superb catch, Stoinis stands his ground and the 3rd umpire will have a look. Was banged in short and hurried him on the pull, hit high on the bat and lobbed towards mid-on - Sanvir ran across, dived in front and managed to get his fingers underneath it, it's confirmed by the 3rd umpire and he sends Stoinis on his way. LSG in early trouble now. Stoinis c Sanvir Singh b Bhuvneshwar 3(5)
Krunal Pandya, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Bhuvneshwar to Krunal Pandya, 1 run, short of a good length and angling across the left-hander, steered away behind square on the on-side for a single
Bhuvneshwar to Rahul, no run, on a good length and shaping back into the right-hander, pushed back at the bowler
Bhuvneshwar to Rahul, no run, back of a length and at the stumps, Rahul plays with a straight bat as he punched it back at the bowler

Bhuvneshwar to Rahul, 1 run, on a good length and just outside off, dabbed with an open face towards backward point, he calls Krunal Pandya across for a quick single and the latter has to scamper to make his ground
Shahbaz Ahmed to Rahul, no run, dropped short by Shahbaz - Rahul backs away and can't beat cover with the cut
Shahbaz Ahmed to Rahul, 2 runs, Shahbaz tosses one on off, Rahul makes room and then places the drive wide of cover, comes back for the second
Shahbaz Ahmed to Rahul, 1 run, tossed up well wide of off, slapped away to the left of long-off for a single
Most Powerplay wickets in IPL 2024 10 Bhuvneshwar Kumar (SR 17.4) 8 Khaleel Ahmed (21.8) 7 Vaibav Arora (14.6) 7 Trent Boult (24.0)
Shahbaz Ahmed to Krunal Pandya, 1 run, tossed up on middle and leg, flicked wide of mid-wicket for a single
Shahbaz Ahmed to Rahul, no run, dropped short and wide of off, cut away straight to the fielder at cover
Shahbaz Ahmed to Rahul, no run, nicely flighted on off, Rahul can't beat cover with the drive - this is LSG's lowest PP score this season
Lowest Powerplay total for LSG in all IPL 27/2 LSG vs SRH Hyderabad 2024 30/1 vs DC Lucknow 2023 30/1 vs SRH Hyderabad 2023

1-6 Over Summary >> Bhuvi Kumar bowls a tight first over >> Rahul hoists Cummins for a six over mid-off >> Nitish Reddy takes a superb catch by the boundary ropes to dismiss de Kock >> Sanvir Singh takes a superb low catch to send back Stoinis >> SRH keep things tight in the powerplay. Just 27 runs conceded.
Time for the Sri Lankan leg-break bowler
Vijayakanth Viyaskanth, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
V Viyaskanth to Krunal Pandya, no run, tossed up on off, Pandya plays with soft hands and drops it to the off-side
V Viyaskanth to Krunal Pandya, 1 run, a cheeky paddle, but Pandya has no pace to work with and dabs it lamely to short third for a run
V Viyaskanth to Rahul, 1 run, dragged short and just outside off, punched down to long-off for a single
V Viyaskanth to Krunal Pandya, no run, shout for LBW, but this has pitched outside leg - Pandya was shaping for the sweep and missed
V Viyaskanth to Krunal Pandya, no run, the wrong 'un now, Pandya picked it and then backed away on the cut, but he can't beat backward point
V Viyaskanth to Krunal Pandya, 1 run, Pandya comes down the pitch and then hoicks it over mid-wicket for a single

Lowest Powerplay totals in IPL 2024 23/3 GT vs RCB Bengaluru 27/3 PK vs SRH Mullanpur 27/2 LSG vs SRH Hyderabad 28/4 MI vs LSG Lucknow 30/4 GT vs DC Ahmedabad - One boundary hit by LSG is the fewest by a team in Powerplay this season.
Jaydev Unadkat, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Unadkat to Krunal Pandya, no run, short of a good length and just outside off, Pandya is cramped for room on the cut and miscues it to the off-side
Unadkat to Krunal Pandya, 2 runs, short and just outside off, doesn't come onto the left-hander and Pandya drags the pull behind square on the on-side, comes back for the second run
Unadkat to Krunal Pandya, no run, another slower short ball from Unadkat, no pace at all and Pandya is way early into the pull, miscues it badly and the ball drops at his feet

Unadkat to Krunal Pandya, SIX, clubbed, a slower short ball once again - Pandya though is ready for this one, waits on it and then plays a forehand swat over mid-on, has enough to clear the ropes for a maximum, much needed for LSG

Unadkat to Krunal Pandya, SIX, cracking shot, overpitched by Unadkat, pace on and Pandya makes most of it - leans forward and swings through the line, a straight bat and the ball went soaring over the ropes for a maximum
STAT: The last time before today a team failed to hit a four in the Powerplay in IPL was RCB against MI in Pune in 2022 (they hit two sixes though).
Unadkat to Krunal Pandya, 1 run, slower bouncer on off, pulled away to deep mid-wicket for a single, 15 off the over, much to LSG's relief

They've taken the strategic break with LSG reeling. The pitch is very slow, the ball is barely coming on and the visitors have struggled to read the conditions. Krunal Pandya was promoted to 4 and that looks like a good move, he too took his time, but has assessed the conditions much better
V Viyaskanth to Krunal Pandya, 1 run, flighted delivery on middle and leg, tucked behind square on the on-side for a single

- 1000+ sixes in IPL 2024 - the third time it has happened in an IPL season after 1062 sixes in 2022 and 1124 in 2023 Fewest balls to 1000 sixes in an IPL edition 13079 in IPL 2024 15390 in IPL 2023 16269 in IPL 2022
V Viyaskanth to Rahul, 1 run, nicely tossed up on middle and leg, punched down to long-off for a single
V Viyaskanth to Krunal Pandya, 1 run, Viyaskanth drifts one on middle and leg, worked wide of mid-wicket for a single
V Viyaskanth to Rahul, no run, the wrong 'un, skids through and cramped Rahul on the cut, mistimed to the off-side
V Viyaskanth to Rahul, 1 run, tossed up on off, driven to the right of cover who makes a smart stop
V Viyaskanth to Krunal Pandya, no run, flighted delivery on leg, punched with a straight bat to mid-wicket
Pat Cummins [1.0-0-10-0] is back into the attack
Cummins to Rahul, FOUR, thumped, much needed for Rahul, he was getting into a rut - pace from Cummins, slightly overpitched as well, drilled over mid-off for the first four of the innings
Cummins to Rahul, 1 run, on a length and at the pads, clipped behind square on the on-side for a single
Cummins to Krunal Pandya, 1 run, full-toss from Cummins, Pandya comes down the pitch and miscues it to long-on
Cummins to Rahul, no run, short of a length and at the stumps - Rahul backs away and can't beat backward point with the cut, Krunal Pandya was sprinting for a quick single and has to rush back
Cummins to Rahul, 2 runs, the slower bouncer from Cummins - Rahul had to reach out as he swatted the pull towards long-on, comes back for the second
Cummins to Rahul, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Cummins to Rahul, out Caught by T Natarajan!! This is a disaster for LSG - Rahul spent a lot of time, he was just starting to push on and he has now holed out to long leg - back of a length and angling into the right-hander, Rahul didn't go full throttle on the pull, he was just looking to help it on its way and ended up lobbing it into the hands of Natarajan, running to his right. LSG lose their captain at the exact halfway mark. KL Rahul c T Natarajan b Cummins 29(33) [4s-1 6s-1]
Nicholas Pooran, left handed bat, comes to the crease
V Viyaskanth to Krunal Pandya, 1 run, flatter and leg-lined, Krunal flicks to deep square leg
V Viyaskanth to Pooran, 1 run, attacks the stumps, Pooran nudges it to the square leg region
V Viyaskanth to Krunal Pandya, 1 run, fullish delivery around off, Krunal drives to long-off
V Viyaskanth to Pooran, FOUR, dragged down and Pooran accepts it happily, stays back and pulls it in front of square, splits the two fielders in the deep perfectly
V Viyaskanth to Pooran, 1 run, low full toss and Pooran eases it down to long-off
V Viyaskanth to Krunal Pandya, no run, slower and no room on offer, Krunal knocks it back to Viyaskanth

Lowest SR in an inngs this IPL (30+ balls) 77.41 T Kotian (24 off 31) vs PK Mullanpur 87.87 KL Rahul (29 off 33) vs SRH Hyderabad 88.88 I Kishan (32 off 36) vs LSG Lucknow 91.17 S Sudharsan (31 off 34) vs PK Mullanpur
T Natarajan, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
T Natarajan to Pooran, 1 run, I0$ fullish delivery outside off, Pooran directs it square on the off-side
SRH are celebrating a run-out. They think Krunal is short of his crease. It was a direct-hit from Cummins. Third umpire called up. One replay is enough. Krunal is OUT
T Natarajan to Krunal Pandya, THATS OUT!! Run Out!!

T Natarajan to Krunal Pandya, out Krunal Pandya Run Out!! Brilliant work by skipper Cummins. Both set batters sent back in a space of 8 balls. Krunal backs away and Natarajan follows him with a full delivery, pushed to mid-off and Krunal decides to risk a single, he sets off and hopes the throw from Cummins is not on target, but for his bad luck the Aussie hits the bullseye and catches him well short of the crease. Krunal Pandya run out (Cummins) 24(21) [6s-2]
Ayush Badoni, right handed bat, comes to the crease
T Natarajan to Pooran, 1 run, on a length and outside off, Pooran throws his bat on the drive and slices it to third man
T Natarajan to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, back of a length around off, Badoni pats it on the head and steers to third man
T Natarajan to Pooran, 1 run, good length ball outside off, Pooran eases it past cover and down to sweeper

Nick Knight on air points out that Pat Cummins was well in from the 30-yard circle when he effected that run-out. He had the head start to get to the ball quicker, got a good bounce as well and he took the middle-stump out of the ground.
T Natarajan to Ayush Badoni, no run, full delivery on off, Badoni stays back and defends with a straight bat
Jaydev Unadkat [1.0-0-15-0] is back into the attack
Unadkat to Pooran, 1 run, I0$ full delivery on off, Pooran drives to long-on

Unadkat to Ayush Badoni, no run, I0$ angled in from back of a length, Badoni turns it to mid-wicket

T Natarajan to Ayush Badoni, FOUR, this is turning into a good over. Natarajan goes round the wicket and angles it in, Badoni shuffles across, gets inside the line and laps it just over Klaasen. Third boundary in the over..

Timeout! Lucknow Super Giants have started to get a move on with 28 runs coming off the last 2 overs. They still have 5 overs to go and should be aiming for a total around 160. That would be challenging on this surface..
Pat Cummins [2.0-0-18-1] is back into the attack

Cummins to Pooran, no run, I0$ fuller and angled across, Pooran throws the kitchen sink on the drive and is beaten on the outside edge

T Natarajan to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, off-pace delivery angled across, Badoni directs it to backward point and calls for a quick single. A direct hit might have had Pooran in trouble at the striker's end
T Natarajan to Pooran, wide, misses the yorker and sprays it down leg, wide called

T Natarajan to Ayush Badoni, FOUR, that's superb batting. Full delivery around off, Badoni shuffles across and sweeps it over square leg. The fielder was brought in and Badoni takes full advantage

T Natarajan to Ayush Badoni, FOUR, Badoni has taken a liking to Natarajan. 5 out of his 6 fours have come against Natarajan. Slower ball outside off, but it was short and Badoni cuts it behind square on the off-side. No chance for the sweeper..
T Natarajan to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, yorker on leg-stump, Badoni digs it to mid-wicket and settles with a single
Bhuvneshwar Kumar [3.0-0-7-2] is back into the attack
Bhuvneshwar to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, fired into the blockhole, Badoni squeezes it out to mid-off and races across
Bhuvneshwar to Pooran, no run, low full toss and Pooran drives it straight to extra cover. Missed out there
Bhuvneshwar to Pooran, 1 run, angled outside off, Pooran slaps the drive to sweeper cover
Bhuvneshwar to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, short and banged into the wicket, Badoni miscues the pull in front of long-on
Bhuvneshwar to Pooran, 1 run, yorker length close to off, Pooran digs it out to mid-off
Bhuvneshwar to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, makes room and Bhuvi follows him with a yorker, jammed out to mid-wicket and Nitish keeps it to a single. An impressive spell from Bhuvi comes to an end - 4-0-12-2

T Natarajan to Ayush Badoni, FOUR, Badoni winning this battle against Natarajan easily. Full and not quite yorker length, Badoni gets under and lifts it over mid-off. Clears the fielder and picks up the boundary
T Natarajan to Ayush Badoni, 2 runs, shortens the length and Badoni pulls it in front of square, between deep mid-wicket and long-on, easy brace
T Natarajan to Ayush Badoni, FOUR, low full toss outside off, Badoni walks across his crease and makes it easy for himself, drives it wide of mid-off and beats the dive of Samad
T Natarajan to Ayush Badoni, no run, nails the wide yorker outside off, Badoni fails to squeeze it out

T Natarajan to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, fifty for Badoni. This has been a fine knock and rightly applauded from everyone in the Lucknow camp. He's given the innings some much needed impetus. Full toss outside off, sliced to deep backward point and Badoni raises his bat to acknowledge the applause
T Natarajan to Pooran, FOUR, another expensive over from Natarajan. 50 from his 4 overs. Full toss down leg, Pooran helps it along the way wide of short fine
Pat Cummins [3.0-0-28-1] is back into the attack
SRH have brought in their impact sub - Abhishek Sharma comes in and Natarajan makes way.

Cummins to Ayush Badoni, FOUR, wow! That's brave from Badoni. He premeditated the reverse lap and though it was a low full toss outside leg-stump, he managed to make a good connection and get it between backward point and short third
Cummins to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, slower short of length delivery, Badoni cuts to deep backward point
Cummins to Pooran, FOUR, full and angled outside off, Pooran throws his bat on the big drive and the thick outside edge flies over short third
Cummins to Pooran, 2 runs, slower ball outside off, Pooran toe-ends the drive to long-off and Badoni races back for the second
Cummins to Pooran, FOUR, I0$ off-pace delivery outside off, Pooran opens the bat face and slices it behind square on the off-side, superb placement as he split backward point and short third
The third umpire is called to check whether it is a six or not. Nitish might have just saved four runs. But the ball has touched the rope and it will be a four

Cummins to Pooran, FOUR, superb effort and Nitish saves a couple. High full toss outside off, below the waist though and Pooran slices it towards sweeper cover. Nitish jumps up and takes the catch but releases the ball as he was coming down, he lands on the rope and falls over, the ball bounces inside the rope and bounces onto the ad cushions, hence a four and not a six

21:15 Local Time, 15:45 GMT: First 10 overs - 57/3. Next 10 overs - 108/1. There are two ways to sum up this innings; the first period when Rahul struggled to get going and the second where Badoni and Pooran showed batting was not that difficult. Lucknow will hope it is the former and that the surface remains the same way. Quinton de Kock and Stoinis fell cheaply, Rahul, barring the six off Cummins, could not get the ball past the 30-yard circle and Krunal got himself in but threw it away via a run-out. The Super Giants were reeling at 66/4 in 11.2 overs when the pair got together. They showed intent right from the start and stitched a crucial 99-run partnership. Badoni got to his fifty while Pooran was denied his by a superb Nitish effort. This looks like a competitive total if the conditions don't change. Back soon with the chase..

Ayush Badoni - The wicket was on the slower side, just wanted to take it deep and just play cricketing shots, didn't want to throw my wicket away. It's not a wicket where you can go from ball 1. The bowlers were bowling short slower balls, so I was looking to find the gap on the shorter square. It's a good score if the dew doesn't come, I think our bowlers will defend it. As of now, there's no dew.

Welcome back for the chase. SRH have made short work of runs while batting first. But will there be any other plans as they look to chase down 166? I doubt. Sharma and Head know one way of playing in the powerplay and they will stick to it. And if they come out trumps with that, this might finish early as SRH do have an eye on their NRR. The floodlights for some reasons had turned off. A few of them I guess had gone off. It is coming back on now. Hence, the delay.An offie to start.
